reviews.review_text:
3-24-95 Great sound!!!!

thanks for sharing this wonderful show
high time great opener couldnt get past high time to depressing.

My first show! I was around 17 at the time. Had a crazy day earlier. Got seperated from my family. Got up with all my oldschool tour kats on the lot. Got up with my family, went in, had a blast! For the most part, Jerry was keeping good time. Few slip-ups, nothing really bad. Whole show sounded awsome inside, the croud really sang more than most copies give you. Packed house, even security and cops were high on something! Great first show! The three I had the chance to see, were great because, I heard most of my favorites. Thanks for a really good time! This copy is very clean, concidering that most from that time period were audience and alot on tapes were pretty rough. You just don't see many soundboards from spring '95. Great job, and lets see some more!

This wasn't just the worst GD show I ever saw.... It was the worst concert I ever saw.

My word that High Time is just dreadful.

First and only This was my first and only Grateful Dead show. I was 16 at the time, and travelled to Charlotte with a high school friend of mine. Man, parents let their kids do anything back then it seems like. I remember running into several kids from my high school there. Such a great memory. I agree not the best sounding show, but I wouldn't say the worst. I give at least four stars.

Worst of three Charlotte shows I attended all three shows, as well as the previous two at the Spectrum.  This show was by far inferior to the other two at Charlotte.  The energy is low, Jerry chops the lyrics on numerous songs. Particularly Bird Song, which is just awful.  Sloppy start, Jerry incoherent at times. Awful.  Hard to listen to. The first two shows, by contrast, had much higher energ, and many more highlights.  In retrospect, it is clear during at least this show Jerry was in really bad shape.  His voice is raspy and weak.  Sound quality of this recording is good, and that's really the only reason I'm giving it three stars.

People got duped... All these ridiculous horrible reviews, so I go in to listen to the show with very low expectations. A few songs then I'm thinking to myself, "what is it right here"... then, as black-throated wind is playing and they get to the part where I know it's an E chord, I walk over to a tune to guitar and I play an E chord and this recording is a half step sharp at least!  Thats a lot ya'll
  It's no wonder the vocals have that chipmunk quality in the music sounds rushed. This isn't what it sounded like! These soundboards need to be taken down and fixed, I don't mean to despair to people who go to the trouble to get these recordings out, but a recording of a concert absolutely must play at the proper speed or else you're listening to something that isn't an accurate representation of what the music actually sounded like and it's not something your ears would adjust for. I'm moving on to a different Source hopefully the other soundboard is in tune and plays at the right speed.
